taff, Senior Administrative Staff and Examination Officers, organized by MOCPED, Noforija on 18th and 19th July, 2007.\r\nvi.	Workshop on the “Harmonious Relationship at Workshop: The Role of Various Stakeholders and “Democracy at Workplace: Myth or Reality” organized by Senior Staff Union of Colleges of Education (SSUCOE), MOCPED branch on 30th April, 2008.\r\nvii.	Train the – Trainers workshop on using Active Learning Techniques in Classroom organized by MOCPED, Noforija on 13th and 14th May, 2008.\r\nviii.	2-Day workshop on the Application of Information and Computer Technology (ICT) in the Production of Semester Results, organized by School of Vocational Education, MOCPED, Noforija on 15th and 16th April, 2009.\r\nix.	Workshop on “Empirical Research” organized by MOCPED, Noforija on 23rd and 24th June, 2009.\r\nx.	Induction Workshop for Senior Staff, employed between January, 2009 to date. Organized by Registry Unit of Yaba College of Technology (YABATECH) on March 23rd and 24th, 2010.\r\nxi.	Seminar on Institutional Effectiveness organized by Internal Quality Assurance Unit (IQA), YABATECH on Friday 18th February, 2011.\r\nxii.	Workshop on Project Development and Management/Professional Research Skills organized by Center for Entrepreneurship Development (CED), YABATECH between 1st and 2nd June, 2011.\r\nxiii.	Conference/Exhibition on The place of Science and Technology (SandT) in Achieving the Millennium Development Goals (MDG’s) organized by Step-B Project and Center for Applied Research and Technology Innovation (ARTI), YABATECH between June 28th and 29th, 2011.\r\nxiv.	Workshop on Operation and Maintenance of Crop Processing Equipment for Entrepreneurs organized by National Centre for Agricultural Mechanization (NCAM) Idofian, Ilorin between September 26th and 30th, 2011.\r\nxv.	Use of Information and Communication Technology (ICT) for Teaching and Research organized by Step-B Project Unit, YABATECH between October 25th and 26th, 2011.\r\nxvi.	Research Project Management organized by Centre for Applied Research and Technology Innovation (ARTI), YABATECH between 19th and 20th June, 2012.\r\nxvii.	Academic Workshop  on Teaching, Research and Publication Management in Higher Education Institutions in Collaboration with College of Teachers at Institute of Education, London and YABATECH on 16th and 18th July, 2013.\r\nxviii.	47th Annual Conference of Agricultural Society of Nigeria (ASN) held at Federal College of Animal Health and Production Technology, Ibadan between 4th and 8th November, 2013.\r\nxix.	9th National Conference on Organic Agriculture in Nigeria held at The Federal University of Agriculture, Abeokuta (FUNAAB) on the 11th and 15th November, 2013.\r\nxx.	Training of Trainers Workshop on the use of SPSS for Teaching and Research Organized by Centre for Applied Research and Technology Innovation (ARTI), YABATECH on 21st and 22nd January, 2015.\r\nxxi.	Management Training Workshop themed: Changing World, New Affiliations and Pragmatic Strategies Organized by McDam Consulting Limited between 14th and 15th March, 2014.\r\nxxii.	Workshop on Duties and Responsibilities of Heads of Departments, Coordinators and Class Advisers organized by Registry Unit, YABATECH on 21st July, 2015.\r\nxxiii.	Intellectual Property Generation, Protection and Management for Growth and Development organized by Centre for Applied Research and Technology Innovation (ARTI), YABATECH on 6th and 7th October, 2015.\r\nxxiv.	2- Day National Leadership Workshop on Inter-Organizational Unity and Synergy: A Paradigm Shift and how to lead for others to follow: strategies in succession Management organized by Global Center for leadership and Human Development, Lagos on 17th and 18th March, 2017. \r\nxxv.	1-Day Workshop on Human Capacity Development organized by The Muslim Congress, Epe Local Government on 28th January, 2018.\r\nxxvi.	2-Day National Leadership Workshop on Sustaining Community Work: The Role of Values Orientation and Strategic Management, organized by Global Center for Leadership and Human Development, Lagos on 16th – 17th March, 2018.\r\nxxvii.	Workshop on “Monitoring of Lower Rank Lecturers” organized by Internal Quality Assurance Unit and Centre for Continuing Professional Development, Yaba College of Technology, Lagos on 8th November, 2018.\r\nxxviii.	Workshop on “Effective Pathway to Grant Winning Proposal Writing” organized by Grantsmanship Committee, Yaba College of Technology, Lagos on 9th November, 2018.\r\nxxix.	In-House Training Programme for Heads of Departments, Class Advisers and Coordinators on “The Role of HODs, Class Advisers and Coordinators in Student Support Services” organized by Staff Development and Training Department, Yaba College of Technology, Lagos between 25th and 26th June, 2019.\r\nxxx.	2019 Fascination of Plants Day on 6th August, 2019 at Federal University of Agriculture, Abeokuta, Ogun State, Nigeria.\r\nxxxi.	Training Programme on “Work Ethics, Etiquette and Leadership” Organized by G International Institute Training Centre for Business and Workplace Skills, (GlobalWIIN), United Kingdom, on 9th and 10th September, 2019.', NULL, '0', NULL, '0', NULL, 'Rosulu, Hamed O. is a native of Epe in Lagos State. An agronomist/entomologist by training, He holds M.Agric. Tech in Crop Production and currently on a PhD programme. An alumnus of Lagos State Polytechnic, Ikorodu and Federal University of Technology, Akure, Ondo State. He started his working career at Michael Otedola College of Primary Education, (MOCPED) Noforija, Epe in May, 1997 and later Yaba College of Technology (YABATECH) in October, 2009. He is a Principal Lecturer and current Head of Department of Agricultural Technology, Yaba College of Technology (YABATECH), Epe campus (since February,2018). He has co-authored two textbooks in the field of Crop Production, published articles in referred journals and presented papers at conferences, both locally and internationally, as well as attended many workshops/seminars. He is an active member of Agricultural Society of Nigeria (ASN) and Organic Agriculture Professionals in Tertiary Institutions in Nigeria (OAPTIN). He is an external examiner to the Department of Agricultural Technology, Lagos State Polytechnic, Ikorodu. Currently, he teaches courses in field experimentation/ Data analysis and Agronomy. He is married and blessed with children.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '01-28', '1');
